Nigeria Plans to Boost Sorghum Output 22% by 2013, Guardian Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-08-18T08:24:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/nigeria-plans-to-boost-sorghum-output-22-by-2013-guardian-says.html
Nigeria plans to raise its annual
sorghum output 22 percent to 11.37 million metric tons by 2013,
the Lagos-based  Guardian reported , citing the chairman of the
Presidential Committee on Sorghum, Abraham Obilana.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 